HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1225
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of David A. Allred of
Celina.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of David A. Allred of Celina; and
WHEREAS, David Allred was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Allred was born on August 19, 1957, in Livingston to Elbert Ray Allred
and Joyce Odeva Copeland Davis; and
WHEREAS, David Allred was a retired former district captain of the Cookeville District of
the Tennessee Highway Patrol and also a member of the Fraternal Order of Police; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Allred was wholly devoted to his family and always endeavored to
remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, he is survived by his daughters, Natasia (Elijah) Cantrell and Brooke
(Michael) Phillips; brothers, Randy (Rene) Davis and Tim (Brenda) Allred; sister, Jackie Danner;
grandchildren, Alyssa Phillips, Colton Phillips, Castellan Cantrell, and Ashton (Mack)
Mutchmore; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his parents, he was preceded in death by his stepfather,
Andrew Thomas Davis, and his son, Adam David Allred; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Allred leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in public
life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
HJR1225
016118
- 1 -

WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should remember the
bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of David A. Allred, reflecting fondly upon his
impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and
conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Allred.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
